A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Entertainment Tourism Alliance of Georgia (ETAG) and recognizing
2 February 28, 2025, as Entertainment Tourism Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Entertainment Tourism Alliance of Georgia (ETAG) is dedicated to
4 promoting and supporting Georgia's thriving entertainment and tourism industries, which
5 significantly contribute to the state's economy, culture, and global reputation; and
6 WHEREAS, Georgia has become a leading destination for film, television, music, digital
7 media, and live entertainment production, generating billions of dollars in economic impact
8 and creating thousands of jobs across the state; and
9 WHEREAS, the state's diverse landscapes, historic sites, world-class production facilities,
10 and skilled workforce have positioned Georgia as a premier location for
11 entertainment-related tourism, drawing visitors from around the world to experience its rich
12 cultural heritage and cinematic attractions; and
13 WHEREAS, ETAG plays a crucial role in fostering collaboration among industry leaders,
14 local businesses, and government officials to ensure continued growth and sustainability in
15 Georgia's entertainment tourism sector; and
