16 WHEREAS, the organization actively promotes initiatives that enhance the visibility of
17 Georgia's entertainment attractions, advocate for policies that support the industry, and
18 provide educational resources for aspiring professionals in the field; and
19 WHEREAS, the economic impact of the state's entertainment tourism industry is significant,
20 and ETAG is working with industry partners to create an economic impact calculator for this
21 robust industry; in addition, ETAG is building a network so that Georgia communities, large
22 and small, have the opportunity to benefit from entertainment tourism; and
23 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to recognize the contributions of ETAG and to celebrate
24 its efforts in strengthening Georgia's status as a top destination for entertainment tourism.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 commend the Entertainment Tourism Alliance of Georgia (ETAG) for its dedication to
27 advancing the entertainment and tourism industries in Georgia and recognize February 28,
28 2025, as Entertainment Tourism Day at the state capitol.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Entertainment
31 Tourism Alliance of Georgia.
